commentText:
By default model attributes are filtered with_{@link HttpMessageWriter#canWrite} to find the ones that can be_rendered. Use this property to further narrow the list and consider only_attribute(s) under specific model key(s)._

If more than one matching attribute is found, than a Map is rendered,_or if the {@code Encoder} does not support rendering a {@code Map} then_an exception is raised.
codeText: public void setModelKeys(Set<String> modelKeys) {_		this.modelKeys.clear()__		if (modelKeys != null) {_			this.modelKeys.addAll(modelKeys)__		}_	}

commentText:
Set the attributes in the model that should be rendered by this view._When set, all other model attributes will be ignored. The matching_attributes are further narrowed with {@link HttpMessageWriter#canWrite}._The matching attributes are processed as follows:_
    _
  • 0: nothing is written to the response body._
  • 1: the matching attribute is passed to the writer._
  • 2..N: if the writer supports {@link Map}, write all matches__otherwise raise an {@link IllegalStateException}._
